Below are internal notes that .... well if you want to read them go right ahead. I want to journal the concept so that when I am ready to build it I can see the architecture.

slide Flick is a frame by frame engine. While there may be interpolation after that is not at all what I am desiging as the core. 
Now if 500 shapes were all moving at once then probably a group or something would be better but we need need to be ready for what I will throw at it. It is correct that 500 shapes will NOT be animated all 720 frames. but a lot will. and if the animation is longer I need to be ready to handle those 20 million characters. If objects can hold it in memory then I am on board. but if we are going to bloat memory by doing this when the shape already has most of the properties and can hold additional ones with tags. I would like us to be cautious of that. I really do like the idea of everything being an object but I dont want to spend the time to make something that takes 4GB of memory when running.


