Ok I am following. so here is a real concept that I didnt even think about.
we were talking about singles earlier right? but. each shape needs to have the 
scrub playback coordinates
the realtime playback coordinates
the tween coordinates
and a few other things

These coordinates are arrays. so are we saying that I actually store arrays as the type of singles for all these properties? I then redim the array size if the user adds an extra frame? Is it that easy?

Im on frame 10 
shape.realtimeLeft(9) = 1.25
shape.realTimeTop(9) = 0

is that it? and it updates the object each time?


EAch shape gets an object that holds this
A shape can absolutely hold multiple arrays of Singles, each representing a different “track” of motion:
* ScrubTrack — the authoritative, baked frame‑by‑frame data
* RealTimeTrack — the values used during playback (may include tween overrides)
* TweenTrack — start/end/easing metadata
* PreviewTrack — optional, for live preview without committing
* LastRecordedTrack — optional, for fill‑forward logic

ReDim Preserve them when the user adds more frames.
“Im on frame 10
shape.realtimeLeft(9) = 1.25
shape.realTimeTop(9) = 0
is that it?”

Yes. That’s literally it.
